   𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∧ 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 \<lsq> A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_jctil)
   from S6 S10 S41 have S42: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 𝟭 \<ls> A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_sylc)
   have S43: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ A \<ca> B ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_nnaddclt)
   have S44: "𝟭 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_1nn)
   have S45: "𝟭 ∈ ℕ ∧ A \<ca> B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<cs> 𝟭 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_nnsubt)
   from S44 S45 have S46: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<cs> 𝟭 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S43 S46 have S47: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   𝟭 \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<cs> 𝟭 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S42 S47 show "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<cs> 𝟭 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
qed

(****** 521,522 *************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nndivt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟷ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_nnne0t)
   from S1 have S2: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   { fix x
     have S3: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ x ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ A⋅x\<cdiv>A = x" by (rule MMI_divcan3t)
     from S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ x ∈ ℂ ⟶ A⋅x\<cdiv>A = x" by (rule MMI_3com23)
     from S4 have S5: "(A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℂ ⟶ A⋅x\<cdiv>A = x" by (rule MMI_3expa)
     have S6: "x ∈ ℕ ⟶ x ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_nncnt)
     from S5 S6 have S7: "(A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ ⟶ A⋅x\<cdiv>A = x" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
     from S7 have S8: "(A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ ⟶ A⋅x\<cdiv>A = x" 
       by (rule MMI_3adantl2)
     from S8 have S9: "(A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ ⟶ x = A⋅x\<cdiv>A" 
       by (rule MMI_eqcomd)
     have S10: "A⋅x = B ⟶ A⋅x\<cdiv>A = B\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
     from S9 S10 have S11: 
       "((A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ) ∧ A⋅x = B ⟶ x = B\<cdiv>A" 
       by (rule MMI_sylan9eq)
     have S12: "((A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ) ∧ A⋅x = B ⟶ 
       (A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
     from S12 have S13: 
       "((A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ) ∧ A⋅x = B ⟶ x ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_pm3_27d)
     from S11 S13 have S14: 
       "((A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬) ∧ x ∈ ℕ) ∧ A⋅x = B ⟶ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" 
       by (rule MMI_eqeltrrd)
     from S14 have "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ x ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
       A⋅x = B ⟶ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_exp31)
     } then have S15: "∀x. A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ x ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
	 A⋅x = B ⟶ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by simp
   from S15 have S16: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟶ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_r19_23adv)
   have S17: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ A⋅(B\<cdiv>A) = B" by (rule MMI_divcan2t)
   have S18: "x = B\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
     A⋅x = A⋅(B\<cdiv>A)" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   from S18 have S19: "x = B\<cdiv>A ⟶ 
     A⋅x = B ⟷ A⋅(B\<cdiv>A) = B" by (rule MMI_eqeq1d)
   from S19 have S20: "B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ∧ A⋅(B\<cdiv>A) = B ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B)" by auto (*(rule MMI_rcla4ev)*)
   from S20 have S21: "A⋅(B\<cdiv>A) = B ⟶ 
     B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B)" by (rule MMI_expcom)
   from S17 S21 have S22: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
     B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S16 S22 have S23: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟷ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_impbid)
   from S23 have S24: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
     B ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
     A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟷ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_3exp)
   from S24 have S25: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
     A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟷ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_imp)
   have S26: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_nncnt)
   have S27: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_nncnt)
   from S25 S26 S27 have S28: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
     A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟷ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   from S2 S28 show "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℕ. A⋅x = B) ⟷ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_mpd)
 qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nndivtrt: 
   shows "(A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ) ∧ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ∧ C\<cdiv>B ∈ ℕ ⟶ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ"
proof -
   have S1: "((B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ) ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>A)⋅(C\<cdiv>B) = (B\<cdiv>B)⋅(C\<cdiv>A)" by (rule MMI_divmul24t)
   have S2: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_nncnt)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_nncnt)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "B ∈ ℕ ∧ A ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_anim12i)
   from S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S5 have S6: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   from S2 have S7: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S7 have S8: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_anim2i)
   from S8 have S9: "B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   from S9 have S10: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_3adant1)
   from S6 S10 have S11: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (B ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ) ∧ C ∈ ℂ ∧ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_jca)
   have S12: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_nnne0t)
   have S13: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_nnne0t)
   from S12 S13 have S14: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_anim12i)
   from S14 have S15: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A ≠ 𝟬 ∧ B ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   from S1 S11 S15 have S16: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>A)⋅(C\<cdiv>B) = (B\<cdiv>B)⋅(C\<cdiv>A)" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S17: "B ∈ ℂ ∧ B ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ B\<cdiv>B = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_dividt)
   from S2 have S18: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" .
   from S13 have S19: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S17 S18 S19 have S20: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ B\<cdiv>B = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S20 have S21: "B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>B)⋅(C\<cdiv>A) = 𝟭⋅(C\<cdiv>A)" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   from S21 have S22: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>B)⋅(C\<cdiv>A) = 𝟭⋅(C\<cdiv>A)" by (rule MMI_3ad2ant2)
   have S23: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divclt)
   from S23 have S24: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_3expb)
   from S3 have S25: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" .
   from S12 have S26: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ A ≠ 𝟬" .
   from S25 S26 have S27: "A ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_jca)
   from S24 S27 have S28: "C ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℕ ⟶ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S28 have S29: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
   have S30: "C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟭⋅(C\<cdiv>A) = C\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_mulid2t)
   from S29 S30 have S31: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟭⋅(C\<cdiv>A) = C\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S31 have S32: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟭⋅(C\<cdiv>A) = C\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_3adant2)
   from S16 S22 S32 have S33: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>A)⋅(C\<cdiv>B) = C\<cdiv>A" by (rule MMI_3eqtrd)
   from S33 have S34: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>A)⋅(C\<cdiv>B) ∈ ℕ ⟷ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
   have S35: "B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ∧ C\<cdiv>B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   (B\<cdiv>A)⋅(C\<cdiv>B) ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_nnmulclt)
   from S34 S35 have S36: "A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ∧ C\<cdiv>B ∈ ℕ ⟶ C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_syl5bi)
   from S36 show 
     "(A ∈ ℕ ∧ B ∈ ℕ ∧ C ∈ ℂ) ∧ B\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ ∧ C\<cdiv>B ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
     C\<cdiv>A ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_imp)
qed

   shows "𝟮 ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   have S2: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S3: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_readdcl)
   from S1 S4 show "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_eqeltr)
qed

   shows "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S2: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S3: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   have S4: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   from S1 S2 S3 S4 have S5: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_addgt0i)
   have S6: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   from S5 S6 show "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_breqtrr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_2p2e4: 
   shows "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟰"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟮 \<ca> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   have S3: "𝟰 = 𝟯 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_4)
   have S4: "𝟯 = 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_3)
   from S4 have S5: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   have S6: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S7: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S8: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S6 S7 S8 have S9: "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟮 \<ca> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S3 S5 S9 have S10: "𝟰 = 𝟮 \<ca> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
   from S2 S10 show "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟰" by (rule MMI_eqtr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_4nn: 
   shows "𝟰 ∈ ℕ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟰" by (rule MMI_2p2e4)
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_2nn)
   have S3: "𝟮 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_2nn)
   have S4: "𝟮 ∈ ℕ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℕ ⟶ 
   𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_nnaddclt)
   from S2 S3 S4 have S5: "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
   from S1 S5 show "𝟰 ∈ ℕ" by (rule MMI_eqeltrr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_2times: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟮⋅A = (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S3 have S4: "(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_1p1times)
   from S2 S4 show "𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_2timest: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A"
proof -
   have S1: "A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A = 𝟮⋅( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_opreq2)
   have S2: "A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S2 have S3: "A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)" .
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A \<ca> A = ( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)) \<ca> ( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_opreq12d)
   from S1 S4 have S5: "A =  if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A ⟷ 
   𝟮⋅( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)) = ( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)) \<ca> ( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_eqeq12d)
   have S6: "𝟬 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_0cn)
   from S6 have S7: " if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬) ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S7 have S8: "𝟮⋅( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)) = ( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬)) \<ca> ( if(A ∈ ℂ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_2times)
   from S5 S8 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_dedth)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_times2: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℂ"   
   shows "A⋅𝟮 = A \<ca> A"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ∈ ℂ".
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   from S1 S2 have S3: "A⋅𝟮 = 𝟮⋅A" by (rule MMI_mulcom)
   from A1 have S4: "A ∈ ℂ".
   from S4 have S5: "𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_2times)
   from S3 S5 show "A⋅𝟮 = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_3p2e5: 
   shows "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟱"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟰 = 𝟯 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_4)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟰 \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟯 \<ca> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   have S3: "𝟱 = 𝟰 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_5)
   have S4: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   from S4 have S5: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟯 \<ca> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   have S6: "𝟯 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3re)
   from S6 have S7: "𝟯 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   have S8: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   have S9: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S7 S8 S9 have S10: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟯 \<ca> (𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S5 S10 have S11: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟯 \<ca> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_eqtr4)
   from S2 S3 S11 show "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟱" by (rule MMI_3eqtr4r)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_3p3e6: 
   shows "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟯 = 𝟲"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟱" by (rule MMI_3p2e5)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟱 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_opreq1i)
   have S3: "𝟯 = 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_3)
   from S3 have S4: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟯 = 𝟯 \<ca> (𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   have S5: "𝟯 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3re)
   from S5 have S6: "𝟯 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   have S7: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S8: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S6 S7 S8 have S9: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭 = 𝟯 \<ca> (𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_addass)
   from S4 S9 have S10: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟯 = 𝟯 \<ca> 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_eqtr4)
   have S11: "𝟲 = 𝟱 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_6)
   from S2 S10 S11 show "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟯 = 𝟲" by (rule MMI_3eqtr4)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_2t2e4: 
   shows "𝟮⋅𝟮 = 𝟰"

   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟮⋅𝟮 = 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2times)
   have S3: "𝟮 \<ca> 𝟮 = 𝟰" by (rule MMI_2p2e4)
   from S2 S3 show "𝟮⋅𝟮 = 𝟰" by (rule MMI_eqtr)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_3t2e6:

   from S2 have S3: "𝟯⋅𝟮 = 𝟯 \<ca> 𝟯" by (rule MMI_times2)
   have S4: "𝟯 \<ca> 𝟯 = 𝟲" by (rule MMI_3p3e6)
   from S3 S4 show "𝟯⋅𝟮 = 𝟲" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_3t3e9: 
   shows "𝟯⋅𝟯 = 𝟵"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟯 = 𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_3)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟯⋅𝟯 = 𝟯⋅(𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_opreq2i)
   have S3: "𝟯 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_3re)
   from S3 have S4: "𝟯 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   have S5: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S4 S5 S6 have S7: "𝟯⋅(𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭) = 𝟯⋅𝟮 \<ca> 𝟯⋅𝟭" by (rule MMI_adddi)
   have S8: "𝟯⋅𝟮 = 𝟲" by (rule MMI_3t2e6)
   from S4 have S9: "𝟯 ∈ ℂ" .
   from S9 have S10: "𝟯⋅𝟭 = 𝟯" by (rule MMI_mulid1)
   from S8 S10 have S11: "𝟯⋅𝟮 \<ca> 𝟯⋅𝟭 = 𝟲 \<ca> 𝟯" by (rule MMI_opreq12i)
   from S7 S11 have S12: "𝟯⋅(𝟮 \<ca> 𝟭) = 𝟲 \<ca> 𝟯" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
   have S13: "𝟲 \<ca> 𝟯 = 𝟵" by (rule MMI_6p3e9)
   from S2 S12 S13 show "𝟯⋅𝟯 = 𝟵" by (rule MMI_3eqtr)
qed

(******** 561-578 ********************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_ltdiv23i: assumes A1: "A ∈ ℝ" and
    A2: "B ∈ ℝ" and
    A3: "C ∈ ℝ" and
    A4: "𝟬 \<ls> B" and
    A5: "𝟬 \<ls> C"   
   shows "A\<cdiv>B \<ls> C ⟷ A\<cdiv>C \<ls> B"
proof -
   from A4 have S1: "𝟬 \<ls> B".
   from A5 have S2: "𝟬 \<ls> C".
   from A1 have S3: "A ∈ ℝ".
   from A2 have S4: "B ∈ ℝ".
   from A3 have S5: "C ∈ ℝ".
   from S3 S4 S5 have S6: "𝟬 \<ls> B ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> C ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>B \<ls> C ⟷ A\<cdiv>C \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_ltdiv23)
   from S1 S2 S6 show "A\<cdiv>B \<ls> C ⟷ A\<cdiv>C \<ls> B" by (rule MMI_mp2an)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_4t2e8: 
   shows "𝟰⋅𝟮 = 𝟴"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟰 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_4re)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟰 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   from S2 have S3: "𝟰⋅𝟮 = 𝟰 \<ca> 𝟰" by (rule MMI_times2)
   have S4: "𝟰 \<ca> 𝟰 = 𝟴" by (rule MMI_4p4e8)
   from S3 S4 show "𝟰⋅𝟮 = 𝟴" by (rule MMI_eqtr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_4d2e2: 
   shows "𝟰\<cdiv>𝟮 = 𝟮"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮⋅𝟮 = 𝟰" by (rule MMI_2t2e4)
   have S2: "𝟰 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_4re)
   from S2 have S3: "𝟰 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recn)
   have S4: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S5: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S6: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S7: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S6 S7 have S8: "𝟮 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   from S3 S4 S5 S8 have S9: "𝟰\<cdiv>𝟮 = 𝟮 ⟷ 𝟮⋅𝟮 = 𝟰" by (rule MMI_divmul)
   from S1 S9 show "𝟰\<cdiv>𝟮 = 𝟮" by (rule MMI_mpbir)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_1lt2: 
   shows "𝟭 \<ls> 𝟮"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟭 \<ls> 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltp1)
   have S3: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   from S2 S3 show "𝟭 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_breqtrr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halfgt0: 
   shows "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>𝟮"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S2: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S1 S2 show "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_recgt0i)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halflt1: 
   shows "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> 𝟭"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟭 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_1cn)
   from S1 have S2: "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 = 𝟭" by (rule MMI_div1)
   have S3: "𝟭 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_1lt2)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_eqbrtr)
   have S5: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S6: "𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ax1re)
   have S7: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S8: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_lt01)
   have S9: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S5 S6 S7 S8 S9 have S10: "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟭 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟷ 
   𝟭\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltdiv23i)
   from S4 S10 show "𝟭\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halfclt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℂ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S3: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "𝟮 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   have S5: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_divclt)
   from S1 S4 S5 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_mp3an23)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_rehalfclt: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S3: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "𝟮 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ A\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_redivclt)
   from S1 S4 S5 show "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mp3an23)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_half0t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S3: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "𝟮 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   have S5: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_diveq0t)
   from S1 S4 S5 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 = 𝟬 ⟷ A = 𝟬" by (rule MMI_mp3an23)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halfpost: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> A"
proof -
   have S1: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<ls> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   have S2: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) = ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_opreq1)
   have S3: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)" by (rule MMI_id)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_breq12d)
   from S1 S4 have S5: "A =  if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ⟶ 
   (𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A) ⟷ 
   𝟬 \<ls> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_bibi12d)
   have S6: "𝟬 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_0re)
   from S6 have S7: " if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_elimel)
   from S7 have S8: "𝟬 \<ls> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬)) ⟷ 
   ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> ( if(A ∈ ℝ, A, 𝟬))" by (rule MMI_halfpos)
   from S5 S8 have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_dedth)
   have S10: "𝟮 = 𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_df_2)
   from S10 have S11: "A\<cdiv>𝟮 = A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭)" by auto (*rule MMI_opreq2i*)
   from S11 have S12: "A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> A ⟷ 
   A\<cdiv>(𝟭 \<ca> 𝟭) \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_breq1i)
   from S9 S12 show "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> A" by (rule MMI_syl6bbr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halfpos2t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>𝟮"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S2: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_gt0divt)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<ls> A ⟷ 𝟬 \<ls> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_mp3an23)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_halfnneg2t: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟷ 𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>𝟮"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S2: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   have S3: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟷ 𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_ge0divt)
   from S1 S2 S3 show "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟬 \<lsq> A ⟷ 𝟬 \<lsq> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_mp3an23)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_2halvest: 
   shows "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ca> A\<cdiv>𝟮 = A"
proof -
   have S1: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_2timest)
   from S1 have S2: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A\<cdiv>𝟮 = (A \<ca> A)\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_opreq1d)
   have S3: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   have S4: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S5: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   from S4 S5 have S6: "𝟮 ≠ 𝟬" by (rule MMI_gt0ne0i)
   have S7: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A\<cdiv>𝟮 = A" by (rule MMI_divcan3t)
   from S3 S6 S7 have S8: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A\<cdiv>𝟮 = A" by (rule MMI_mp3an13)
   have S9: "𝟮 ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_2cn)
   from S6 have S10: "𝟮 ≠ 𝟬" .
   have S11: "(A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℂ) ∧ 𝟮 ≠ 𝟬 ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> A)\<cdiv>𝟮 = A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ca> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_divdirt)
   from S10 S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> A)\<cdiv>𝟮 = A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ca> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S9 S12 have S13: "A ∈ ℂ ∧ A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> A)\<cdiv>𝟮 = A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ca> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_mp3an3)
   from S13 have S14: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> A)\<cdiv>𝟮 = A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ca> A\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_anidms)
   from S2 S8 S14 show "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
   A\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ca> A\<cdiv>𝟮 = A" by (rule MMI_3eqtr3rd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_nominpos: 
   shows "¬( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ ¬( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x))"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   { fix x
     have S3: "(x ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮" 
       by (rule MMI_divgt0t)
     from S3 have S4: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_ex)
     from S2 S4 have S5: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
     from S1 S5 have S6: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_mpan2i)
     have S7: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟷ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_halfpost)
     from S7 have S8: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_biimpd)
     from S6 S8 have S9: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∧ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_jcad)
     have S10: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_rehalfclt)
     from S9 S10 have S11: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ 
       x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∧ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_jctild)
     have S12: "y = x\<cdiv>𝟮 ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> y ⟷ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     have S13: "y = x\<cdiv>𝟮 ⟶ 
       y \<ls> x ⟷ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S12 S13 have S14: "y = x\<cdiv>𝟮 ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x ⟷ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∧ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
     from S14 have S15: "x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> x\<cdiv>𝟮 ∧ x\<cdiv>𝟮 \<ls> x ⟶ 
       ( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x)" by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4ev*)
     from S11 S15 have S16: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ 
       ( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_syl6)
     have S17: "(𝟬 \<ls> x ⟶ 
       ( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       ¬(𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ ¬( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_iman)
     from S16 S17 have "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       ¬(𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ ¬( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_sylib)
     } then have  S18: "∀ x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       ¬(𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ ¬( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x))" by simp
   from S18 show "¬( ∃x∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> x ∧ ¬( ∃y∈ℝ. 𝟬 \<ls> y ∧ y \<ls> x))" 
     by (rule MMI_nrex)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_avglet: 
   shows "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ∨ (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B"
proof -
   have S1: "𝟮⋅A ∈ ℝ ∧ A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ 
   ¬(A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A)" by (rule MMI_ltnlet)
   have S2: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S3: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_axmulrcl)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S4 have S5: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   have S6: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_axaddrcl)
   from S1 S5 S6 have S7: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ 
   ¬(A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A)" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S8: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltadd2t)
   have S9: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_26)
   have S10: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
   from S9 have S11: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S8 S9 S10 S11 have S12: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   have S13: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ca> B \<ls> B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_ltadd1t)
   from S9 have S14: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S10 have S15: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S10 have S16: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S13 S14 S15 S16 have S17: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ls> B ⟷ A \<ca> B \<ls> B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl3anc)
   from S12 S17 have S18: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ A \<ca> B \<ls> B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_bitr3d)
   have S19: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   have S20: "A ∈ ℂ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_2timest)
   from S19 S20 have S21: "A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S21 have S22: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅A = A \<ca> A" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S22 have S23: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ A \<ca> A \<ls> A \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq1d)
   have S24: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   have S25: "B ∈ ℂ ⟶ 𝟮⋅B = B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_2timest)
   from S24 S25 have S26: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅B = B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S26 have S27: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅B = B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S27 have S28: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<ls> 𝟮⋅B ⟷ A \<ca> B \<ls> B \<ca> B" by (rule MMI_breq2d)
   from S18 S23 S28 have S29: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟷ A \<ca> B \<ls> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_3bitr4d)
   have S30: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮⋅B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<ls> 𝟮⋅B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_ltlet)
   from S6 have S31: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" .
   have S32: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S33: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_axmulrcl)
   from S32 S33 have S34: "B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpan)
   from S34 have S35: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 𝟮⋅B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantl)
   from S30 S31 S35 have S36: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<ls> 𝟮⋅B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S29 S36 have S37: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   𝟮⋅A \<ls> A \<ca> B ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S7 S37 have S38: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A) ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_sylbird)
   from S38 have S39: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A ∨ A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_orrd)
   have S40: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S41: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   have S42: "(A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A" by (rule MMI_ledivmult)
   from S41 S42 have S43: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S40 S43 have S44: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ A ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A" by (rule MMI_mp3an2)
   from S6 have S45: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S9 have S46: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A ∈ ℝ" .
   from S44 S45 S46 have S47: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S48: "𝟮 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_2re)
   have S49: "𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮" by (rule MMI_2pos)
   have S50: "(A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ 𝟬 \<ls> 𝟮 ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_ledivmult)
   from S49 S50 have S51: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ 𝟮 ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_mpan2)
   from S48 S51 have S52: "A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_mp3an2)
   from S6 have S53: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ A \<ca> B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S10 have S54: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" .
   from S52 S53 S54 have S55: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S47 S55 have S56: "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ∨ (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅A ∨ A \<ca> B \<lsq> 𝟮⋅B" by (rule MMI_orbi12d)
   from S39 S56 show "A ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> A ∨ (A \<ca> B)\<cdiv>𝟮 \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lbreu: 
   shows "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y))"
proof -
  { fix x w
    have S1: "y = w ⟶ 
      x \<lsq> y ⟷ x \<lsq> w" by (rule MMI_breq2)
    from S1 have S2: "w ∈ S ⟶ 
      (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ x \<lsq> w" by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4v*)
    have S3: "y = x ⟶ 
      w \<lsq> y ⟷ w \<lsq> x" by (rule MMI_breq2)
    from S3 have S4: "x ∈ S ⟶ 
      (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ w \<lsq> x" by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4v*)
    from S2 S4 have S5: "x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x \<lsq> w ∧ w \<lsq> x" 
      by (rule MMI_im2anan9r)
    have S6: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ S ⟶ x ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
    have S7: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      w ∈ S ⟶ w ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
    from S6 S7 have S8: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_anim12d)
    from S8 have S9: "(x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S) ∧ S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_impcom)
    have S10: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      x = w ⟷ x \<lsq> w ∧ w \<lsq> x" by (rule MMI_letri3t)
    from S9 S10 have S11: "(x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S) ∧ S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x = w ⟷ x \<lsq> w ∧ w \<lsq> x" by (rule MMI_syl)
    from S11 have S12: "(x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S) ∧ S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x \<lsq> w ∧ w \<lsq> x ⟶ x = w" by (rule MMI_biimprd)
    from S12 have S13: "x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x \<lsq> w ∧ w \<lsq> x ⟶ x = w" by (rule MMI_ex)
    from S13 have S14: "x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      x \<lsq> w ∧ w \<lsq> x ⟶ 
      S ⊆ℝ ⟶ x = w" by (rule MMI_com23)
    from S5 S14 have S15: "x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
      S ⊆ℝ ⟶ x = w" by (rule MMI_syld)
    from S15 have "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x = w" by (rule MMI_com3r)
  } then have S16: "∀x w . S ⊆ℝ ⟶ x ∈ S ∧ w ∈ S ⟶ 
      (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x = w" by auto
  from S16 have S17: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    (∀x∈S. ∀w∈S. (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x = w)" 
    by auto (*rule MMI_r19_21aivv*)
  from S17 have S18: "( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀x∈S. ∀w∈S. (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x = w)" 
    by (rule MMI_anim2i)
  from S18 have S19: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀x∈S. ∀w∈S. (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x = w)" 
    by (rule MMI_ancoms)
  have S20: "∀x. x = w ⟶  x \<lsq> y ⟷ w \<lsq> y" by auto (*rule MMI_breq1*)
  from S20 have S21: "∀ x. x = w ⟶ 
    (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y)" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
  from S21 have S22: "(∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ⟷ 
    ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀x∈S. ∀w∈S. (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟶ x = w)" 
     by auto  (*rule MMI_reu4*)
   from S19 S22 show "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y))" by auto (*rule MMI_sylibr*)
 qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lbcl: 
   shows "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S"
proof -
   have S1: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y))" by (rule MMI_lbreu)
   have S2: "(∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" by (rule MMI_reucl2)
   have S3: "{x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⊆S" by (rule MMI_ssrab2)
   from S3 have S4: "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_sseli)
   from S1 S2 S4 show "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_3syl)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lble: 
   shows "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ A ∈ S ⟶ 
   (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A"
proof -
   have S1: "(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∀y. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_hbra1)
   { fix w
     have S2: "w ∈ S ⟶ (∀y. w ∈ S)" by (rule MMI_ax_17)
     from S1 S2 have S3: "w ∈ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀y. w ∈ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by auto (*rule MMI_hbrab*)
     from S3 have "w ∈ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀y. w ∈ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by (rule MMI_hbuni)
   } then have S4: "∀w. w ∈ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀y. w ∈ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by simp
       (*have S5: "w ∈ <_ ⟶ (∀y. w ∈ <_)" by (rule MMI_ax_17)
       have S6: "w ∈ A ⟶ (∀y. w ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_ax_17) *)
   have S7: "(⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A ⟶ 
     (∀y. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A)" by auto
   have S8: "y = A ⟶ 
     (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y ⟷ 
     (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_breq2)
   from S7 S8 have S9: "A ∈ S ⟶ 
     (∀y∈S. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4*)
   from S9 have S10: "A ∈ S ∧ (∀y∈S. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_imp)
   have S11: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y))" by (rule MMI_lbreu)
   have S12: "x = w ⟶ 
     x \<lsq> y ⟷ w \<lsq> y" by (rule MMI_breq1)
   from S12 have S13: "x = w ⟶ 
     (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y)" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
   from S13 have S14: "(∃!x. x∈S∧(∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ⟷ 
     (∃!w. w∈S∧(∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y))" by auto (*rule MMI_cbvreuv*)
   from S11 S14 have S15: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (∃!w. w∈S∧(∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y))" by (rule MMI_sylib)
   { fix w x
     have S16: "w = x ⟶ 
       w \<lsq> y ⟷ x \<lsq> y" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S16 have "w = x ⟶ 
       (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟷ (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
   } then have S17: "∀w x. w = x ⟶ 
       (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟷ (∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)" by simp
   from S4 have S18: "∀ w. w ∈ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
   (∀y. w ∈ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" .
   from S18 have S19: "∀w. w = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
   (∀y. w = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by auto (*rule MMI_hbeleq*)
   { fix w
     have S20: "w = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       w \<lsq> y ⟷ 
       (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S19 S20 have "w = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀y∈S. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y)" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbid*)
   } then have S21: "∀ w. w = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀y∈S. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y)" by simp
   from S17 S21 have S22: "(∃!w. w∈S∧(∀y∈S. w \<lsq> y)) ⟶ 
   (∀y∈S. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_reuuni3)
   from S15 S22 have S23: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∀y∈S. (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S10 S23 have S24: "A ∈ S ∧ S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
   from S24 have S25: "A ∈ S ∧ S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_3impb)
   from S25 show "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ A ∈ S ⟶ 
   (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_3coml)
qed

(************* proven by hand **********************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_df_sup: shows
  "Sup(B,A,\<cltrrset>) = ⋃ {x ∈ A. (∀y∈B. ¬(x\<ls>y) ) ∧ 
  (∀y∈A. y\<ls>x  ⟶ (∃z∈B. y\<ls>z))}"
  using Sup_def cltrr_def by simp

(** not really in the Metamath, but needed **)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_df_inf: shows
  "Sup(B,A,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = ⋃ {x ∈ A. (∀y∈B. ¬(x > y) ) ∧ 
  (∀y∈A. y > x  ⟶ (∃z∈B. y > z))}"
  using Sup_def convcltrr_def by simp

(********* 579 ******************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lbinfm: 
   shows "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }"
proof -
  { fix z
    have S1: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> z" by (rule MMI_lble)
    from S1 have S2: "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> z" by (rule MMI_3expa)
    have S3: "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ ∧ z ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> z ⟷ 
      ¬(z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }))" by (rule MMI_lenltt)
    have S4: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
      ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_lbcl)
    have S5: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S ⟶ 
      ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel2)
    from S4 S5 have S6: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
      ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syldan)
    from S6 have S7: "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
    have S8: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel2)
    from S8 have S9: "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" 
      by (rule MMI_adantlr)
    from S3 S7 S9 have S10: "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> z ⟷ 
      ¬(z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }))" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
    from S2 S10 have S11: "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      ¬(z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }))" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
    have S12: "ℝ = ℝ" by (rule MMI_reex)
    from S12 have S13: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ S = S" by (rule MMI_ssex)
    have S14: "S = S ⟶ 
      {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } = {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" by auto (*rule MMI_rabexg*)
    from S13 S14 have S15: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } = {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" by (rule MMI_syl)
    have S16: "{x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } = {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
      ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
      by auto(*rule MMI_uniexg*)
      (*have S17: "z = z" by simp;*) (*rule MMI_visset*)
    have S18: "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∧ z = z ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z ⟷ 
      z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by (rule MMI_brcnvg)
    from S18 have S19: "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ V ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z ⟷ 
      z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by auto (*rule MMI_mpan2*)
    from S15 S16 S19 have S20: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z ⟷ 
      z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" 
      using cltrr_def convcltrr_def converse_iff by auto(*rule MMI_3syl*)
    from S20 have S21: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z) ⟷ 
      ¬(z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }))" by (rule MMI_negbid)
    from S21 have S22: "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z) ⟷ 
      ¬(z \<ls> (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }))" by (rule MMI_ad2antrr)
    from S11 S22 have "(S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
      ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
    } then have S23: "∀z. (S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y)) ∧ z ∈ S ⟶ 
	¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)" by simp
     from S23 have S24: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z))" by (rule MMI_r19_21aiva)
   have S25: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_lbcl)
   { fix z
     from S25 have S26: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ 
       ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_a1d)
     from S26 have S27: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ 
       ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S ∧ z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" 
       by (rule MMI_ancrd)
     have S28: "w = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶  z > w ⟷ 
       z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" by auto (*rule MMI_breq2*)
     from S28 have S29: 
       "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S ∧ z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)" 
       by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4ev*)
     from S27 S29 have S30: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)" by (rule MMI_syl6)
     from S30 have "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       z ∈ ℝ ⟶  z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)" 
       by (rule MMI_a1d)
   } then have S31: "∀ z. S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       z ∈ ℝ ⟶  z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)" by simp
       (*{ fix v
       { fix z*)
   from S31 have S32: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" 
     by (rule MMI_r19_21aiv)
   from S24 S32 have S33: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ 
     ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" by (rule MMI_jca)
   { fix v
     { fix z 
       have S34: "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶  v > z ⟷  
	 (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z" by auto (*rule MMI_breq1*)
       from S34 have "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
	 ¬(v > z) ⟷ 
	 ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)" by (rule MMI_negbid)
     } then have S35: "∀ z. v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
	 ¬(v > z) ⟷  ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)" by simp
     from S35 have S36: "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ⟷ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z))" by (rule MMI_ralbidv)
     { fix z
       have S37: "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
	 z > v ⟷   z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y })" 
	 by auto (*rule MMI_breq2*)
       from S37 have S38: "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
	 (z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
	 (z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" 
	 by (rule MMI_imbi1d)
     } then have S38: "∀z. v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
	 (z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
	 (z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" by simp
     from S38 have S39: "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
       (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" 
       by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
     from S36 S39 have "v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
       (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" 
       by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   } then have S40: "∀v. v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
       (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
       (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" by simp
   from S40 have S41: "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ ∧ 
     (∃!v. v∈ℝ∧(∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))) ⟶ 
     (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
     (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ 
     ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) } = 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
     by (rule MMI_reuuni2)
   have S42: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_lbcl)
   have S43: "S ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S ⟶ 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
   from S43 have S44: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S ⟶ 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S42 S44 have S45: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpd)
   from S40 have S46: "∀v. v = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ⟶ 
   (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
   (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
     (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" .
   from S46 have S47: 
     "⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ ∧ 
     (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
     (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟶ 
   ( ∃v∈ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)))" 
     by (rule MMI_rcla4ev)
   from S45  have S48: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ ℝ" by auto
   from S33 have S49: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
     (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w))" by auto
   from S47 S48 S49 have S50: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ( ∃v∈ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S51: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   have S52: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ ⟷ converse(\<cltrrset>) Orders ℝ" 
     by (rule MMI_cnvso)
   from S51 S52 have S53: "converse(\<cltrrset>) Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
   from S53 have S54: "( ∃v∈ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ 
     ( ∃w∈S. z > w))) ⟶ (∃!v. v∈ℝ∧(∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ 
     ( ∃w∈S. z > w)))" 
     by (rule MMI_infeu)
   from S50 S54 have S55: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∃!v. v∈ℝ∧(∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)))" 
     by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S41 S45 S55 have S56: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   (∀z∈S. ¬((⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) > z)) ∧ 
     (∀z∈ℝ. z > (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) ⟷ 
   ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) } = 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
     by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S33 S56 have S57: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) } = 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
     by (rule MMI_mpbid)
   have S58: 
     "Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  = 
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀z∈S. ¬(v > z)) ∧ (∀z∈ℝ. z > v ⟶ ( ∃w∈S. z > w)) }" 
     by (rule MMI_df_inf)
   from S57 S58 show "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  = 
     ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" by (rule MMI_syl5eq)
qed

(******** 580-581*******************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lbinfmcl: 
  shows 
  "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶  
  Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) ∈ S"
proof -
  have S1: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
    by (rule MMI_lbinfm)
  have S2: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y } ∈ S" by (rule MMI_lbcl)
  from S1 S2 show 
    "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶  Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  ∈ S"
    by (rule MMI_eqeltrd)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_lbinfmle: 
   shows 
  "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ A ∈ S ⟶  
  Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  \<lsq> A"
proof -
  have S1: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
    by (rule MMI_lbinfm)
  from S1 have S2: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ A ∈ S ⟶ 
    Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = ⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }" 
    by (rule MMI_3adant3)
  have S3: "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ A ∈ S ⟶ 
    (⋃ {x ∈ S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y }) \<lsq> A" by (rule MMI_lble)
  from S2 S3 show 
    "S ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃x∈S. ∀y∈S. x \<lsq> y) ∧ A ∈ S ⟶  
    Sup(S,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>))  \<lsq> A" 
    by (rule MMI_eqbrtrd)
qed

(******** 582 ***********************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_sup2: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))"
proof -
  { fix x
    have S1: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_peano2re)
    from S1 have S2: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
    from S2 have S3: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_a1i)
    { fix y
      have S4: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟶ y ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
      have S5: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ∧ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_axlttrn)
      from S5 have S6: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ∧ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_3expb)
      from S1 have S7: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" .
      from S7 have S8: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ∧ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ancli)
      from S6 S8 have S9: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∧ x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
      have S10: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ltp1t)
      from S9 S10 have S11: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_sylan2i)
      from S11 have S12: "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_exp4b)
      from S12 have S13: "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_com34)
      from S13 have S14: "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_pm2_43d)
      from S14 have S15: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_imp)
      from S10 have S16: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" .
      have S17: "y = x ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟷ x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_breq1)
      from S17 have S18: "x \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
	y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_biimprcd)
      from S16 S18 have S19: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_syl)
      from S19 have S20: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_adantl)
      from S15 S20 have S21: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∨ y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_jaod)
      from S21 have S22: "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∨ y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_ex)
      from S4 S22 have S23: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∨ y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_syl6)
      from S23 have S24: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∨ y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_com23)
      from S24 have S25: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟶ 
	y \<ls> x ∨ y = x ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_imp)
      from S25 have "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	(y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_a2d)
    } then have S26: "∀ y. A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	(y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by simp
    from S26 have S27: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_19_20dv)
    have S28: "(∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟷ 
      (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
    have S29: "(∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭) ⟷ 
      (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
    from S27 S28 S29 have S30: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_3imtr4g)
    from S30 have S31: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_ex)
    from S31 have S32: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_imp3a)
    from S3 S32 have S33: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_jcad)
    have S34: "x \<ca> 𝟭 = x \<ca> 𝟭" by auto (*rule MMI_oprex*)
    have S35: "z = x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
      z ∈ ℝ ⟷ x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
    have S36: "z = x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
      y \<ls> z ⟷ y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭" by (rule MMI_breq2)
    from S36 have S37: "z = x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
    from S35 S37 have S38: "z = x \<ca> 𝟭 ⟶ 
      z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z) ⟷ 
      x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭)" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
    from S34 S38 have S39: "x \<ca> 𝟭 ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x \<ca> 𝟭) ⟶ 
      ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z))" by auto (*rule MMI_cla4ev*)
    from S33 S39 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z))" by (rule MMI_syl6)
  } then have S40: "∀ x. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
      ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z))" by auto
  from S40 have S41: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    ( ∃x. x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)) ⟶ 
    ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z))" by (rule MMI_19_23adv)
  have S42: "z = x ⟶ 
    z ∈ ℝ ⟷ x ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
  have S43: "z = x ⟶ 
    y \<ls> z ⟷ y \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_breq2)
  from S43 have S44: "z = x ⟶ 
    (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z) ⟷ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
  from S42 S44 have S45: "z = x ⟶ 
    z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z) ⟷ 
    x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
  from S45 have S46: "( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> z)) ⟷ 
    ( ∃x. x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x))" by auto (*rule MMI_cbvexv*)
  from S41 S46 have S47: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    ( ∃x. x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x. x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_syl6ib)
   have S48: "( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟷ 
   ( ∃x. x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x))" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
   have S49: "( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x) ⟷ 
   ( ∃x. x ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
   from S47 S48 S49 have S50: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_3imtr4g)
   from S50 have S51: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S51 have S52: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   (A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_imdistani)
   have S53: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟷ 
   (A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_df_3an)
   have S54: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x) ⟷ 
   (A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_df_3an)
   from S52 S53 S54 have S55: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_3imtr4)
   have S56: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_axsup)
   from S55 S56 show "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_syl)
qed

(************* 583 *************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_sup3: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))"
proof -
   have S1: "A ≠ 0 ⟷ ¬(A = 0)" by (rule MMI_df_ne)
   from S1 have S2: "¬(A = 0) ⟷ A ≠ 0" by (rule MMI_bicomi)
   from S2 have S3: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A = 0) ⟷ A ≠ 0" by (rule MMI_a1i)
   { fix x
     { fix y
       have S4: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ y ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
       have S5: "y ∈ ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       y \<lsq> x ⟷ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x" by (rule MMI_leloet)
       from S5 have S6: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y \<lsq> x ⟷ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x" by (rule MMI_expcom)
       from S4 S6 have S7: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ 
	 y \<lsq> x ⟷ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x" by (rule MMI_syl9)
       from S7 have "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ) ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ 
	 y \<lsq> x ⟷ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x" by (rule MMI_imp31)
     } then have S8: "∀y. (A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ) ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ 
	 y \<lsq> x ⟷ y \<ls> x ∨ y = x" by simp
     from S8 have "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
       (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
   } then have S9: "∀x. A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
       (∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by simp
   from S9 have S10: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_rexbidva)
   from S3 S10 have S11: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
     A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   from S11 have S12: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
     A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_pm5_32i)
   have S13: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
   A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)" by (rule MMI_3anass)
   have S14: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟷ 
   A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_3anass)
   from S12 S13 S14 have S15: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟷ 
   A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x)" by (rule MMI_3bitr4)
   have S16: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ A ≠ 0 ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<ls> x ∨ y = x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup2)
   from S15 S16 show "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sylbi)
qed

(******* 584 **********************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_infm3lem: 
   shows "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃y∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>y))"
proof -
   have S1: "y = (\<cn>x) ⟶ (\<cn>y) = (\<cn>(\<cn>x))" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   from S1 have S2: "y = (\<cn>x) ⟶ 
   x = (\<cn>y) ⟷ x = (\<cn>(\<cn>x))" by (rule MMI_eqeq2d)
   from S2 have S3: "(\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ ∧ x = (\<cn>(\<cn>x)) ⟶ 
   ( ∃y∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>y))" by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4ev*)
   have S4: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   have S5: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
   have S6: "x ∈ ℂ ⟶ (\<cn>(\<cn>x)) = x" by (rule MMI_negnegt)
   from S5 S6 have S7: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>(\<cn>x)) = x" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S7 have S8: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x = (\<cn>(\<cn>x))" by (rule MMI_eqcomd)
   from S3 S4 S8 show "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃y∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>y))" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
qed

(******** 585 ********************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_infm3: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)))"
proof -
  { fix v
    have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      v ∈ A ⟶ v ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
    from S1 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      v ∈ A ⟷ 
      v ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ A" by (rule MMI_pm4_71rd)
  } then have S2: "∀ v. A ⊆ℝ ⟶  v ∈ A ⟷  v ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ A" by simp
  from S2 have S3: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    ( ∃v. v ∈ A) ⟷ 
    ( ∃v. v ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ A)" by auto (*rule MMI_exbidv*)
   have S4: "( ∃v∈ℝ. v ∈ A) ⟷ 
   ( ∃v. v ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
   { fix w
     have "w ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>w) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   } then have S5: "∀w. w ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>w) ∈ ℝ" by simp
   { fix v
     have "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       ( ∃w∈ℝ. v = (\<cn>w))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
   } then have S6: "∀ v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃w∈ℝ. v = (\<cn>w))" by simp
   { fix v w
     have  "v = (\<cn>w) ⟶ 
       v ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>w) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
   } then have S7: "∀v w. v = (\<cn>w) ⟶ v ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>w) ∈ A"
     by simp
   from S5 S6 S7 have S8: "( ∃v∈ℝ. v ∈ A) ⟷ 
   ( ∃w∈ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_rexxfr)
   from S4 S8 have S9: "( ∃v. v ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ A) ⟷ 
   ( ∃w∈ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_bitr3)
   from S3 S9 have S10: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃v. v ∈ A) ⟷ 
   ( ∃w∈ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
   have S11: "¬(A = 0) ⟷ ( ∃v. v ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_n0)
   have S12: "¬({w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } = 0) ⟷ 
   ( ∃w∈ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_rabn0)
   from S10 S11 S12 have S13: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A = 0) ⟷ 
   ¬({w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_3bitr4g)
   { fix x
     { fix y
       have S14: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ y ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
       from S14 have S15: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟷ 
	 y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A" by (rule MMI_pm4_71rd)
       from S15 have S16: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 (y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_imbi1d)
       have S17: "(y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_impexp)
       from S16 S17 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 (y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
     } then have S18: "∀y. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 (y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by simp
     from S18 have S19: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_albidv)
     have S20: "(∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     { fix v
       have  "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>v) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
     } then have S21: "∀ v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>v) ∈ ℝ" by simp
     { fix y
       have "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ( ∃v∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
     } then have S22: "∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃v∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>v))"
       by simp
     { fix y v
       have S23: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>v) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1)   
       have S24: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 x \<lsq> y ⟷ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
       from S23 S24 have "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 (y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
     } then have S25: "∀ y v. y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ (y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by simp
     from S21 S22 S25 have S26: "(∀y∈ℝ. y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_ralxfr)
     have S27: "(∀y∈ℝ. y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶  y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     from S26 S27 have S28: "(∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       y ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_bitr3)
     from S19 S20 S28 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by auto (*rule MMI_3bitr4g*)
   } then have S29: "∀ x. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by simp
   from S29 have S30: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" 
     by (rule MMI_rexbidv)
   { fix u
     have "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   } then have S31: "∀ u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" by simp
   { fix x
     have S32: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃u∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
   } then have S32: "∀ x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃u∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>u))" by simp
   { fix x u
     have S33: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       x \<lsq> (\<cn>v) ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S33 have S34: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
       ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
     from S34 have S35: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" 
       by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
   } then have S35: "∀x u. x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by simp
   from S31 S32 S35 have S36: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
   ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" 
     by (rule MMI_rexxfr)
   { fix u
     { fix v
       have S37: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 v \<lsq> u ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_lenegt)
       from S37 have S38: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 v \<lsq> u ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
       from S38 have S39: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
     } then have  S39: "∀ v. u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by simp
     from S39 have S40: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
     have S41: "w = v ⟶ (\<cn>w) = (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_negeq)
     from S41 have S42: "w = v ⟶ 
       (\<cn>w) ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>v) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
     from S42 have S43: "v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟷ 
       v ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>v) ∈ A" by auto (*rule MMI_elrab*)
     from S43 have S44: "(v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (v ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_imbi1i)
     have S45: "(v ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_impexp)
     from S44 S45 have S46: "(v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_bitr)
     from S46 have S47: "(∀v. v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u)" by auto (*rule MMI_albii*)
     have S48: "(∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v. v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     have S49: "(∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     from S47 S48 S49 have S50: "(∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_3bitr4r)
     from S40 S50 have "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_syl5bbr)
   } then have S51: "∀ u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" by simp
   from S51 have S52: "( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u) ⟷ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>u) \<lsq> (\<cn>v))" 
     by (rule MMI_rexbiia)
   from S36 S52 have S53: "( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_bitr4)
   from S30 S53 have S54: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
   from S13 S54 have S55: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟷ 
     ¬({w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u)" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   have S56: "{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssrab2)
   have S57: "{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬({w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u) ⟶ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)))" by (rule MMI_sup3)
   from S56 S57 have S58: 
     "¬({w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. ∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<lsq> u) ⟶ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)))" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
   from S55 S58 have S59: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)))" by (rule MMI_syl6bi)
   { fix x
     { fix y
       have S60: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟷ 
	 y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A" using MMI_ssel MMI_pm4_71rd by simp
       from S60 have S61: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_imbi1d)
       have S62: "(y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_impexp)
       from S61 S62 have S63: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶  (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
     } then have S63: "∀y. A ⊆ℝ ⟶  (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
	 (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by simp
     from S63 have S64: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_albidv)
     have S65: "(∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     { fix v
       have "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>v) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
     } then have S66: "∀ v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>v) ∈ ℝ" by simp
     { fix y
       have S67: "y ∈ ℝ ⟶  ( ∃v∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>v))"  by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
     } then have S67: "∀ y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶  ( ∃v∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>v))" by simp
     { fix y v
       have S68: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶  y ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>v) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
       have S69: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 y \<ls> x ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_breq1)
       from S69 have S70: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ¬(y \<ls> x) ⟷ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_negbid)
       from S68 S70 have "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
     } then have S71: "∀y v. y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x))" by simp
     from S66 S67 S71 have S72: "(∀y∈ℝ. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_ralxfr)
     have S73: "(∀y∈ℝ. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     from S72 S73 have S74: "(∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_bitr3)
     from S64 S65 S74 have S75: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_3bitr4g)
     have S76: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       z ∈ A ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
     { fix v
       from S76 have S77: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantrd)
       from S77 have S78: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟷ 
	 z ∈ ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_pm4_71rd)
       from S78 have S79: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z. z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by auto (*rule MMI_exbidv*)
       have S80: "( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃z. z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
       { fix t
	 have "t ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>t) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
       } then have  S81: "∀ t. t ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>t) ∈ ℝ" by simp
       { fix z
	 have "z ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃t∈ℝ. z = (\<cn>t))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
       } then have S82: "∀ z. z ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃t∈ℝ. z = (\<cn>t))" by simp
       { fix z t
	 have S83: "z = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	   z ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>t) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
	 have S84: "z = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	   z \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟷ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq1)
	 from S83 S84 have S85: "z = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	   z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟷ 
	   (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
       } then have S85: "∀z t. z = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	   z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟷ 
	   (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by simp
       from S81 S82 S85 have S86: "( ∃z∈ℝ. z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_rexxfr)
       have S87: "( ∃z∈ℝ. z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
       from S86 S87 have S88: "( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃z. z ∈ ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ∧ z \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_bitr3)
       from S79 S80 S88 have S89: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_3bitr4g)
       from S89 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
	 (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
     } then have  S90: "∀ v. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	 (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
	 (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by auto
     from S90 have S91: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_ralbidv)
     { fix v
       have "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>v) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
     } then have S92: "∀ v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>v) ∈ ℝ" by simp
     { fix y
       have "y ∈ ℝ ⟶  ( ∃v∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
     } then have S93: "∀ y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶  ( ∃v∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>v))" by simp
     { fix y v
       have S94: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶  x \<ls> y ⟷ x \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
       { fix z
	 have "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	   z \<ls> y ⟷ z \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
       } then have S95: "∀ z. y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	   z \<ls> y ⟷ z \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by simp
       from S95 have S96: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_rexbidv)
       from S94 S96 have S97: "y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 (x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
	 (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
     } then have S97: "∀ y v. y = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 (x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
	 (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by simp
     from S92 S93 S97 have S98: "(∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_ralxfr)
     from S91 S98 have S99: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_syl5bb)
     from S75 S99 have S100: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   } then have S100: "∀x. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by simp
   from S100 have S101: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))) ⟷ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
     ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))))" by (rule MMI_rexbidv)
   { fix u
     have "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   } then have S102: "∀ u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" by simp
   { fix x
     have "x ∈ ℝ ⟶  ( ∃u∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
   } then have S103: "∀ x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶  ( ∃u∈ℝ. x = (\<cn>u))" by simp
   { fix x u
     have S104: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) \<ls> x ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     from S104 have S105: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x) ⟷ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_negbid)
     from S105 have S106: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
     from S106 have S107: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
     have S108: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq1)
     from S108 have S109: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
       ((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi1d)
     from S109 have S110: "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
     from S107 S110 have "x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
     } then have S111: "∀x u. x = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by simp
   from S102 S103 S111 have S112: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))) ⟷ 
   ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
   ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))))" by (rule MMI_rexxfr)
   { fix u
     { fix v
       have S113: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 u \<ls> v ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_ltnegt)
       from S113 have S114: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ¬(u \<ls> v) ⟷ 
	 ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_negbid)
       from S114 have "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
	 ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
     } then have S115: "∀ v. u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
	 ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by simp
     from S115 have S116: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
     have S117: "v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟷ 
       v ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>v) ∈ A" using MMI_negeq  MMI_eleq1d by auto
     from S117 have S118: "(v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (v ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v))" by (rule MMI_imbi1i)
     have S119: "(v ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v))" by (rule MMI_impexp)
     from S118 S119 have S120: "(v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v))" by (rule MMI_bitr)
     from S120 have S121: "(∀v. v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v))" by auto (*rule MMI_albii*)
     have S122: "(∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v. v ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     have S123: "(∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v. v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
     from S121 S122 S123 have S124: "(∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v))" by (rule MMI_3bitr4r)
     from S116 S124 have S125: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_syl5bbr)
     { fix v 
       have S126: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 v \<ls> u ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_ltnegt)
       from S126 have S127: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 v \<ls> u ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
       { fix t
	 have S128: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ t ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	   v \<ls> t ⟷ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_ltnegt)
	 from S128 have "v ∈ ℝ ∧ t ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	   (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ v \<ls> t ⟷ 
	   (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_anbi2d)
       } then have S129: "∀ t. v ∈ ℝ ∧ t ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	   (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ v \<ls> t ⟷ 
	   (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by simp
       from S129 have S130: "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ v \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_rexbidva)
       have S131: "w = t ⟶ (\<cn>w) = (\<cn>t)" by (rule MMI_negeq)
       from S131 have S132: "w = t ⟶ 
	 (\<cn>w) ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>t) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
       from S132 have S133: "t ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ⟷ 
	 t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A" by auto (*rule MMI_elrab*)
       from S133 have S134: "t ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ∧ v \<ls> t ⟷ 
	 (t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A) ∧ v \<ls> t" by (rule MMI_anbi1i)
       have S135: "(t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A) ∧ v \<ls> t ⟷ 
	 t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ v \<ls> t" by (rule MMI_anass)
       from S134 S135 have S136: "t ∈ {w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A } ∧ v \<ls> t ⟷ 
	 t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ v \<ls> t" by (rule MMI_bitr)
       from S136 have S137: "( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ v \<ls> t)" by auto (*rule MMI_rexbii2*)
       from S130 S137 have S138: "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_syl5bb)
       from S138 have S139: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_adantl)
       from S127 S139 have "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 (v \<ls> u ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
     } then have S140: "∀ v. u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 (v \<ls> u ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
	 ((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
	 ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by simp
     from S140 have S141: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
     (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
     from S125 S141 have S142: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   } then have S142: "∀ u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
       (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
       ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by simp
   from S142 have S143: 
     "( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t))) ⟷ 
     ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
     ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v))))" by (rule MMI_rexbiia)
   from S112 S143 have S144: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀v∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟶ 
     ¬((\<cn>v) \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. x \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))) ⟷ 
   ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)))" by (rule MMI_bitr4)
   from S101 S144 have S145: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))) ⟷
