   ( ∃u∈ℝ. (∀v∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. ¬(u \<ls> v)) ∧ (∀v∈ℝ. v \<ls> u ⟶ 
   ( ∃t∈{w ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>w) ∈ A }. v \<ls> t)))" by (rule MMI_syl6bb)
   from S59 S145 have S146: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sylibrd)
   from S146 show "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)))" 
     by (rule MMI_3impib)
qed

(***** 586,587 ****************************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprcl: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3)
   have S2: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   from S2 have S3: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_supcl)
   from S1 S3 show "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprub: 
   shows "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ 
  B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) "
proof -
   have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3)
   have S2: " \<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   from S2 have S3: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))) ⟶ 
   B ∈ A ⟶ ¬( Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_supub)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   B ∈ A ⟶ 
   ¬( Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S4 have S5: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ 
   ¬( Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_imp)
   have S6: "B ∈ ℝ ∧  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ⟷ 
   ¬( Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  \<ls> B)" by (rule MMI_lenltt)
   have S7: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ A ⊆ℝ" 
     by (rule MMI_3simp1)
   from S7 have S8: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   B ∈ A ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_sseld)
   from S8 have S9: 
     "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ B ∈ ℝ" 
     by (rule MMI_imp)
   have S10: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_suprcl)
   from S10 have S11: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantr)
   from S6 S9 S11 have S12: 
     "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ 
   B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  ⟷ ¬( Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)  \<ls> B)" 
     by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   from S5 S12 show 
     "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ 
     B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
qed

(********** 588 - 590 *****************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprlub: 
   shows  "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
  ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ⟶ 
  ( ∃z∈A. B \<ls> z)"
proof -
   have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3)
   have S2: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   from S2 have S3: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))) ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. B \<ls> z)" 
     by (rule MMI_suplub)
   from S1 S3 have S4: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. B \<ls> z)" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S4 show "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ⟶ 
     ( ∃z∈A. B \<ls> z)" by (rule MMI_imp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprnub: 
   shows "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
  ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))"
proof -
  have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
    ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
    by (rule MMI_sup3)
  have S2: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
  from S2 have S3: 
    "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))) ⟶ 
    B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
    ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_supnub)
  from S1 S3 have S4: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
    B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
    ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_syl)
  from S4 show "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
    ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_imp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprleub: 
   shows 
  "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B"
proof -
  { fix z
    have S1: "z ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      z \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬(B \<ls> z)" by (rule MMI_lenltt)
    have S2: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel2)
    from S1 S2 have S3: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ A) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      z \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬(B \<ls> z)" by (rule MMI_sylan)
    from S3 have "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ 
      z \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬(B \<ls> z)" by (rule MMI_an1rs)
  } then have S4: "∀z. (A ⊆ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ) ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ 
      z \<lsq> B ⟷ ¬(B \<ls> z)" by simp
  from S4 have S5: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟷ 
    (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z))" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
  from S5 have S6: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟷ 
   (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z))" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S6 have S7: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟷ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z))" by (rule MMI_pm5_32d)
   from S7 have S8: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟷ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z))" by (rule MMI_3ad2ant1)
   have S9: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
     ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_suprnub)
   have S10: " Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_lenltt)
   have S11: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_suprcl)
   from S10 S11 have S12: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_sylan)
   from S12 have S13: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B ⟷ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_adantrr)
   from S9 S13 have S14: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_mpbird)
   from S14 have S15: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_ex)
   from S8 S15 have S16: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_sylbid)
   from S16 show "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_imp)
qed

(************** 591 - 595 ******************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_sup3i: 
  assumes A1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)"   
   shows " ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)".
   have S2: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z)))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3)
   from S1 S2 show 
     " ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))" 
     by (rule MMI_ax_mp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprcli: 
  assumes A1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)"   
   shows " Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   from A1 have S2: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)".
   from S2 have S3: 
     " ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3i)
   from S1 S3 show " Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_supcli)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprubi: 
  assumes A1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)"   
   shows "B ∈ A ⟶ 
   B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)".
   have S2: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ A ⟶ 
   B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)" by (rule MMI_suprub)
   from S1 S2 show "B ∈ A ⟶ 
   B \<lsq>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>)" by (rule MMI_mpan)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprlubi: 
  assumes A1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)"   
  shows "B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. B \<ls> z)"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   from A1 have S2: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)".
   from S2 have S3: 
     "∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3i)
   from S1 S3 show "B ∈ ℝ ∧ B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. B \<ls> z)" 
     by (rule MMI_suplubi)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprnubi: 
  assumes A1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)"   
   shows "B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))"
proof -
   have S1: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   from A1 have S2: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)".
   from S2 have S3: 
     "∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x \<ls> y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y \<ls> x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y \<ls> z))" 
     by (rule MMI_sup3i)
   from S1 S3 show "B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. ¬(B \<ls> z)) ⟶ 
   ¬(B \<ls>  Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_supnubi)
qed

(************ 596 - 598 ***********************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_suprleubi: 
  assumes A1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)"   
   shows "B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B"
proof -
   from A1 have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)".
   have S2: 
     "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. y \<lsq> x)) ∧ B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_suprleub)
   from S1 S2 show "B ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀z∈A. z \<lsq> B) ⟶ 
    Sup(A,ℝ,\<cltrrset>) \<lsq> B" by (rule MMI_mpan)
qed  

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_reuunineg: assumes 
  A1: "∀x y. x = (\<cn>y) ⟶  φ(x) ⟷ ψ(y)"   
   shows "(∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ φ(x)) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. φ(x) } = (\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) }))"
proof -
  let ?C = "\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) })"
  { fix z
    have S1: "z ∈ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) } ⟶ 
      (∀y. z ∈ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) })" by (rule MMI_hbrab1)
    from S1 have S2: "z ∈ ⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) } ⟶ 
      (∀y. z ∈ ⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) })" by (rule MMI_hbuni)
    from S2 have "z ∈ (\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) })) ⟶ 
      (∀y. z ∈ (\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) })))" by (rule MMI_hbneg)
  } then have S3: "∀ z. z ∈ ?C ⟶ (∀y. z ∈ ?C)" by simp
  { fix y
    have "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>y) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
  } then have S4: "∀ y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>y) ∈ ℝ" by simp
   have S5: "⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) } ∈ ℝ ⟶ ?C ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   from A1 have S6: "∀x y.  x = (\<cn>y) ⟶  φ(x) ⟷ ψ(y)" .
   { fix y
     have "y = ⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) } ⟶ 
       (\<cn>y) = (\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) }))" by (rule MMI_negeq)
   } then have S7: "∀ y. y = ⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) } ⟶ 
       (\<cn>y) = (\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) }))" by simp
   { fix x
     have "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   } then have S8: "∀ x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ" by simp
   { fix x y
     have S9: "x ∈ ℂ ∧ y ∈ ℂ ⟶ 
       x = (\<cn>y) ⟷ y = (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_negcon2t)
     have S10: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ x ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
     have S11: "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ y ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
     from S9 S10 S11 have "x ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       x = (\<cn>y) ⟷ y = (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_syl2an)
   } then have S12: "∀x y. x ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       x = (\<cn>y) ⟷ y = (\<cn>x)" by simp
   from S8 S12 have S13: "∀x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
   (∃!y. y∈ℝ∧x = (\<cn>y))" by (rule MMI_reuhyp)
   from S3 S4 S5 S6 S7 S13 show "(∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ φ(x)) ⟶ 
   ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. φ(x) } = (\<cn>(⋃ {y ∈ ℝ. ψ(y) }))" by (rule MMI_reuunixfr)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_dfinfmr: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ⟶  Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = 
  ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) }"
proof -
  { fix x
    { fix y
      have S1: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	x \<lsq> y ⟷ ¬(y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_lenltt)
      have S2: "x = x" by simp (*rule MMI_visset&*)
      have S3: "y = y" by simp (*rule MMI_visset*)
      from S2 S3 have S4: "x > y ⟷ y \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_brcnv)
      from S4 have S5: "¬(x > y) ⟷ ¬(y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_negbii)
      from S1 S5 have S6: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	¬(x > y) ⟷ x \<lsq> y" by auto (*rule MMI_syl6rbbr*)
      have S7: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ y ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel2)
      from S6 S7 have S8: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ A ⊆ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ 
	¬(x > y) ⟷ x \<lsq> y" by (rule MMI_sylan2)
      from S8 have S9: "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ y ∈ A) ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	¬(x > y) ⟷ x \<lsq> y" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
      from S9 have "(A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ) ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ 
	¬(x > y) ⟷ x \<lsq> y" by (rule MMI_an1rs)
    } then have S10: "∀ y. (A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ) ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ 
	¬(x > y) ⟷ x \<lsq> y" by simp
    from S10 have S11: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ⟷ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y)" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
    { fix y::i
      have S12: "y = y" by simp
      have S13: "x = x" by simp
      from S12 S13 have S14: "y > x ⟷ x \<ls> y" by (rule MMI_brcnv)
      have S15: "y = y" by simp
      { fix z::i
	have S16: "z = z" by simp
	from S15 S16 have S17: "y > z ⟷ z \<ls> y" by (rule MMI_brcnv)
      } then have  S17: "∀ z. y > z ⟷ z \<ls> y" by simp
      from S17 have S18: "( ∃z∈A. y > z) ⟷ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)" by (rule MMI_rexbii)
      from S14 S18 have "(y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
	(x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_imbi12i)
    } then have  S19: "∀ y. (y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
	(x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))" by simp
    from S19 have S20: "(∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_ralbii)
    from S20 have S21: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_a1i)
    from S11 S21 have S22: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))" 
      by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
    from S22 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))" 
      by (rule MMI_ex)
  } then have S23: "∀ x. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y))"
    by simp
  from S23 have S24: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) } = 
    {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) }" 
    by (rule MMI_rabbidv)
  from S24 have S25: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) } = 
    ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) }" 
    by (rule MMI_unieqd)
  have S26: "Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = 
    ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. y > z)) }" 
    by (rule MMI_df_inf)
  from S25 S26 show "A ⊆ℝ ⟶  Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = 
    ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃z∈A. z \<ls> y)) }" 
    by (rule MMI_syl5eq)
qed

(******* 599,600 *****************************)

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_infmsup: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))"
proof -
  have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)))" 
    by (rule MMI_infm3)
  from S1 have S2: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
    ¬(A = 0) ⟶ 
    ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
    ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)))" 
    by (rule MMI_3exp)
  { fix x v
    have S3: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      y \<ls> x ⟷ y \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
    from S3 have S4: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      ¬(y \<ls> x) ⟷ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_negbid)
    from S4 have S5: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
    have S6: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      x \<ls> y ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> y" by (rule MMI_breq1)
    from S6 have S7: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      (x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
      ((\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_imbi1d)
    from S7 have S8: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
    from S5 S8 have S9: "x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" 
      by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
  } then have S9: "∀ x v. x = (\<cn>v) ⟶ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" 
    by simp
  from S9 have S10: 
    "(∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))) ⟶ 
    ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) } = 
    (\<cn>(⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ 
    ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }))" by (rule MMI_reuunineg)
  have S11: "Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = 
   ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) }" by (rule MMI_df_inf)
  { fix x::i 
    { fix y::i 
      have S12: "x = x" by simp (*rule MMI_visset*)
      have S13: "y = y" by simp (*rule MMI_visset*)
      from S12 S13 have S14: "x > y ⟷ y \<ls> x" by (rule MMI_brcnv)
      from S14 have S15: "¬(x > y) ⟷ ¬(y \<ls> x)" by (rule MMI_negbii)
    } then have  S15: "∀ y. ¬(x > y) ⟷ ¬(y \<ls> x)" by simp
    from S15 have S16: "(∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x))" by (rule MMI_ralbii)
    { fix y::i
      have S17: "y = y" by simp
      have S18: "x = x" by simp
      from S17 S18 have S19: "y > x ⟷ x \<ls> y" by (rule MMI_brcnv)
      have S20: "y = y" by simp
      { fix w::i
	have S21: "w = w" by simp (*rule MMI_visset*)
	from S20 S21 have S22: "y > w ⟷ w \<ls> y" by (rule MMI_brcnv)
      } then have  S22: "∀ w. y > w ⟷ w \<ls> y" by simp
      from S22 have S23: "( ∃w∈A. y > w) ⟷ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)" by (rule MMI_rexbii)
      from S19 S23 have "(y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
	(x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_imbi12i)
    } then have S24: "∀y.(y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
	(x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by simp
    from S24 have S25: "(∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_ralbii)
    from S16 S25 have "(∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" 
      by (rule MMI_anbi12i)
  } then have S26: "∀x. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by simp
  then have S27: "∀ x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
    (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
    (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by simp
    from S27 have S28: 
      "{x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) } = 
      {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }" 
      by (rule MMI_rabbii)
    from S28 have S29: 
      "⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) } = 
      ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }" 
      by (rule MMI_unieqi)
    from S11 S29 have S30: "Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = 
      ⋃ {x ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }" 
      by (rule MMI_eqtr)
    from S10 S30 have S31: 
      "(∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))) ⟶ 
      Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = 
      (\<cn>(⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ 
      ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }))" by (rule MMI_syl5eq)
    { fix v
      { fix u
	have S32: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	  v \<ls> u ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_ltnegt)
	from S32 have S33: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	  ¬(v \<ls> u) ⟷ 
	  ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_negbid)
	from S33 have "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	  ((\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
	  ((\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
	  ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
    } then have  S34: "∀ u. v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	((\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
	((\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by simp
    from S34 have S35: "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
      ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
    have S36: "z = u ⟶ (\<cn>z) = (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_negeq)
    from S36 have S37: "z = u ⟶ 
      (\<cn>z) ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>u) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
    from S37 have S38: "u ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ⟷ 
      u ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>u) ∈ A" by auto (*rule MMI_elrab*)
    from S38 have S39: "(u ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (u ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u))" by (rule MMI_imbi1i)
    have S40: "(u ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u))" by (rule MMI_impexp)
    from S39 S40 have S41: "(u ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u))" by (rule MMI_bitr)
    from S41 have S42: "(∀u. u ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (∀u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u))" by auto (*rule MMI_albii*)
    have S43: "(∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (∀u. u ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
    have S44: "(∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (∀u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
    from S42 S43 S44 have S45: "(∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u))" by (rule MMI_3bitr4r)
    from S35 S45 have S46: "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
      ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_syl5bbr)
    { fix u
      have S47: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	u \<ls> v ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_ltnegt)
      from S47 have S48: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	u \<ls> v ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_ancoms)
      { fix t
	have S49: "u ∈ ℝ ∧ t ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	  u \<ls> t ⟷ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_ltnegt)
	from S49 have "u ∈ ℝ ∧ t ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	  (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ u \<ls> t ⟷ 
	  (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_anbi2d)
      } then have S50: "∀ t. u ∈ ℝ ∧ t ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	  (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ u \<ls> t ⟷ 
	  (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by simp
      from S50 have S51: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ u \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_rexbidva)
      have S52: "z = t ⟶ (\<cn>z) = (\<cn>t)" by (rule MMI_negeq)
      from S52 have S53: "z = t ⟶ 
	(\<cn>z) ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>t) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
      from S53 have S54: "t ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ⟷ 
	t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A" by auto (*rule MMI_elrab*)
      from S54 have S55: "t ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ∧ u \<ls> t ⟷ 
	(t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A) ∧ u \<ls> t" by (rule MMI_anbi1i)
      have S56: "(t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A) ∧ u \<ls> t ⟷ 
	t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ u \<ls> t" by (rule MMI_anass)
      from S55 S56 have S57: "t ∈ {z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A } ∧ u \<ls> t ⟷ 
	t ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ u \<ls> t" by (rule MMI_bitr)
      from S57 have S58: "( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ u \<ls> t)" by auto (*rule MMI_rexbii2*)
      from S51 S58 have S59: "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_syl5bb)
      from S59 have S60: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t) ⟷ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_adantl)
      from S48 S60 have S61: "v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	(u \<ls> v ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
	((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
    } then have S61: "∀ u. v ∈ ℝ ∧ u ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	(u \<ls> v ⟶ ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
	((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))"
      by simp
    from S61 have S62: "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
      ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
      ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_ralbidva)
    from S46 S62 have S63: "v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
      ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
      ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
      ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
    have S64: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟶ y ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
    from S64 have S65: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟷ 
      y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A" by (rule MMI_pm4_71rd)
    from S65 have S66: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi1d)
    have S67: "(y ∈ ℝ ∧ y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_impexp)
    from S66 S67 have S68: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      (y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_syl6rbb)
    from S68 have S69: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by auto (*rule MMI_albidv*)
    { fix u
      have "u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
    } then have S70: "∀ u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" by simp
    { fix y
      have "y ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃u∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
    } then have S71: "∀ y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃u∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>u))" by simp
    { fix y u
      have S72: "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	y ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>u) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
      have S73: "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	y \<ls> (\<cn>v) ⟷ (\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)" by (rule MMI_breq1)
      from S73 have S74: "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)) ⟷ 
	¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v))" by (rule MMI_negbid)
      from S72 S74 have S75: "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	(y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
	((\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
	¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
    } then have S75: "∀y u. y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	(y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ ((\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶  ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" 
      by simp
    from S70 S71 S75 have S76: "(∀y∈ℝ. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
      ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_ralxfr)
    have S77: "(∀y∈ℝ. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
    from S76 S77 have S78: "(∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
      ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (∀y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
      y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_bitr3)
    have S79: "(∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (∀y. y ∈ A ⟶ ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_df_ral)
    from S69 S78 S79 have S80: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
      ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ⟷ 
      (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v)))" by (rule MMI_3bitr4g)
    { fix u
      have S81: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	w ∈ A ⟶ w ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
      from S81 have S82: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ w ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_adantrd)
      from S82 have S83: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟷ 
	w ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_pm4_71rd)
      from S83 have S84: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	( ∃w. w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u)) ⟷ 
	( ∃w. w ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by auto (*rule MMI_exbidv*)
      have S85: "( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u)) ⟷ 
	( ∃w. w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
      { fix t
	have S86: "t ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>t) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
      } then have S86: "∀ t. t ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>t) ∈ ℝ" by simp
      { fix w
	have S87: "w ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃t∈ℝ. w = (\<cn>t))" by (rule MMI_infm3lem)
      } then have S87: "∀ w. w ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃t∈ℝ. w = (\<cn>t))" by simp
      { fix w t
	have S88: "w = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	  w ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>t) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1)
	have S89: "w = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	  w \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟷ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_breq1)
	from S88 S89 have S90: "w = (\<cn>t) ⟶ 
	  w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟷ 
	  (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
      } then have  S90: "∀ w t. w = (\<cn>t) ⟶  w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟷ 
	  (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by simp
      from S86 S87 S90 have S91: "( ∃w∈ℝ. w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u)) ⟷ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_rexxfr)
      have S92: "( ∃w∈ℝ. w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u)) ⟷ 
	( ∃w. w ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_df_rex)
      from S91 S92 have S93: "( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)) ⟷ 
	( ∃w. w ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ A ∧ w \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_bitr3)
      from S84 S85 S93 have S94: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u)) ⟷ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_3bitr4g)
      from S94 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ⟷ 
	((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_imbi2d)
    } then have S95: "∀ u. A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
	((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ⟷ 
       ((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by simp
    from S95 have S96: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
      ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ⟷ 
      (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
      ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_ralbidv)
    from S70 have S97: "∀ u. u ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>u) ∈ ℝ" .
    from S71 have S98: "∀ y. y ∈ ℝ ⟶ ( ∃u∈ℝ. y = (\<cn>u))" .
    { fix y u
      have S99: "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	(\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟷ (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
      { fix w
	have "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	  w \<ls> y ⟷ w \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
      } then have S100: "∀ w. y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	  w \<ls> y ⟷ w \<ls> (\<cn>u)" by simp
      from S100 have S101: "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
	( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y) ⟷ 
	( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u))" by (rule MMI_rexbidv)
     from S99 S101 have "y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ((\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
       ((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_imbi12d)
   } then have S102: "∀ y u. y = (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ((\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
       ((\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
       ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by simp
   from S97 S98 S102 have S103: "(∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) ⟷ 
     (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
     ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> (\<cn>u)))" by (rule MMI_ralxfr)
   from S96 S103 have S104: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ⟷ 
     (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" by (rule MMI_syl5rbb)
   from S80 S104 have S105: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>u) ∈ A ⟶ 
     ¬((\<cn>u) \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> (\<cn>u) ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈ℝ. (\<cn>t) ∈ A ∧ (\<cn>t) \<ls> (\<cn>u))) ⟷ 
     (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" 
     by (rule MMI_anbi12d)
   from S63 S105 have S106: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
     (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
     (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan9bbr)
   from S106 have S107: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶  v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
     (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
     (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" 
     by (rule MMI_ex)
 } then have S107: "∀ v. A ⊆ℝ ⟶  v ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
     (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) ⟷ 
     (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))"
   by simp
   from S107 have S108: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     {v ∈ ℝ. (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) } = 
     {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ 
     ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }" by (rule MMI_rabbidv)
   from S108 have S109: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶  
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) } = 
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ 
     (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }" by (rule MMI_unieqd)
   have S110: "Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>) = 
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀u∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. ¬(v \<ls> u)) ∧ (∀u∈ℝ. u \<ls> v ⟶ 
     ( ∃t∈{z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A }. u \<ls> t)) }" by (rule MMI_df_sup)
   from S109 S110 have S111: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>) = 
     ⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ 
     (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }" by (rule MMI_syl5eq)
   from S111 have S112: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
     (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>)) = 
     (\<cn>(⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ 
     (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) }))" by (rule MMI_negeqd)
   from S112 have S113: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   (\<cn>(⋃ {v ∈ ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> (\<cn>v))) ∧ 
     (∀y∈ℝ. (\<cn>v) \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)) })) = 
     (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" by (rule MMI_eqcomd)
   from S31 S113 have S114: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ (∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ 
     (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))) ⟶ 
     Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" 
     by (rule MMI_sylan9eqr)
   from S114 have S115: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   (∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" 
     by (rule MMI_ex)
   have S116: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_ltso)
   have S117: "\<cltrrset> Orders ℝ ⟷ converse(\<cltrrset>) Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_cnvso)
   from S116 S117 have S118: "converse(\<cltrrset>) Orders ℝ" by (rule MMI_mpbi)
   from S118 have S119: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w))) ⟶ 
     (∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)))" 
     by (rule MMI_infeu)
   (*from S26 have S120: "(∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
     (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" .;*)
   from (*S120*) S26 have S121: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w))) ⟷ 
     ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)))" 
     by (rule MMI_rexbii)
   from S26 have S122: "∀ x. (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w)) ⟷ 
   (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))" .
   from S122 have S123: 
     "(∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(x > y)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. y > x ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. y > w))) ⟷ 
   (∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)))" 
     by (rule MMI_reubii)
   from S119 S121 S123 have S124: 
     "( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))) ⟶ 
   (∃!x. x∈ℝ ∧ (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y)))" 
     by (rule MMI_3imtr3)
   from S115 S124 have S125: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. (∀y∈A. ¬(y \<ls> x)) ∧ (∀y∈ℝ. x \<ls> y ⟶ ( ∃w∈A. w \<ls> y))) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" 
     by (rule MMI_syl5)
   from S2 S125 have S126: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
   ¬(A = 0) ⟶ 
   ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" 
     by (rule MMI_syl6d)
   from S126 show "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({z ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>z) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" 
     by (rule MMI_3imp)
qed

lemma (in MMIsar0) MMI_infmrcl: 
   shows "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) ∈ ℝ"
proof -
   have S1: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
   Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) = (\<cn>Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>))" 
     by (rule MMI_infmsup)
   have S2: "{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⊆ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssrab2)
   have S3: "{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z) ⟶ 
     Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_suprcl)
   from S2 S3 have S4: "¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0) ∧ 
     ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z) ⟶ 
     Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_mp3an1)
   { fix z
     have S5: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       z ∈ A ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel)
     have S6: "z ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>z) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
     from S5 S6 have S7: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       z ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>z) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl6)
     have S8: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ z ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_ssel2)
     have S9: "z ∈ ℝ ⟶ z ∈ ℂ" by (rule MMI_recnt)
     have S10: "z ∈ ℂ ⟶ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) = z" by (rule MMI_negnegt)
     from S8 S9 S10 have S11: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) = z" by (rule MMI_3syl)
     have S12: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ z ∈ A" by (rule MMI_pm3_27)
     from S11 S12 have S13: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ z ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eqeltrd)
     from S13 have S14: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       z ∈ A ⟶ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_ex)
     from S7 S14 have S15: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ 
       z ∈ A ⟶ 
       (\<cn>z) ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_jcad)
     have S16: "v = (\<cn>z) ⟶ (\<cn>v) = (\<cn>(\<cn>z))" by (rule MMI_negeq)
     from S16 have S17: "v = (\<cn>z) ⟶ 
       (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
     from S17 have S18: "(\<cn>z) ∈ {v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⟷ 
       (\<cn>z) ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) ∈ A" by auto (*rule MMI_elrab*)
     have S19: "(\<cn>z) ∈ {v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⟶ 
       ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_n0i)
     from S18 S19 have S20: "(\<cn>z) ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>(\<cn>z)) ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_sylbir)
     from S15 S20 have "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ z ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_syl6)
   } then have S21: "∀ z. A ⊆ℝ ⟶  z ∈ A ⟶ 
       ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by simp
   from S21 have S22: "A ⊆ℝ ⟶ ( ∃z. z ∈ A) ⟶ 
     ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_19_23adv)
   from S22 have S23: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ( ∃z. z ∈ A) ⟶ 
     ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_imp)
   have S24: "¬(A = 0) ⟷ ( ∃z. z ∈ A)" by (rule MMI_n0)
   from S23 S24 have S25: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ⟶ 
     ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_sylan2b)
   from S25 have S26: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     ¬({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } = 0)" by (rule MMI_3adant3)
   { fix x
     { fix w
       have S27: "y = (\<cn>w) ⟶ 
	 x \<lsq> y ⟷ x \<lsq> (\<cn>w)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
       from S27 have S28: "(\<cn>w) ∈ A ∧ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>w)" 
	 by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4va*)
       from S28 have S29: 
	 "(w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A) ∧ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ x \<lsq> (\<cn>w)" 
	 by (rule MMI_adantll)
       from S29 have S30: 
	 "(x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A) ∧ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
	 x \<lsq> (\<cn>w)" by (rule MMI_adantll)
       have S31: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 x \<lsq> (\<cn>w) ⟷ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_lenegcon2t)
       from S31 have S32: "x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A ⟶ 
	 x \<lsq> (\<cn>w) ⟷ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_adantrr)
       from S32 have S33: "(x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A) ∧ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
	 x \<lsq> (\<cn>w) ⟷ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_adantr)
       from S30 S33 have S34: 
	 "(x ∈ ℝ ∧ w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A) ∧ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
	 w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_mpbid)
       from S34 have S35: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A ⟶ 
	 (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_exp31)
       have S36: "v = w ⟶ (\<cn>v) = (\<cn>w)" by (rule MMI_negeq)
       from S36 have S37: "v = w ⟶ 
	 (\<cn>v) ∈ A ⟷ (\<cn>w) ∈ A" by (rule MMI_eleq1d)
       from S37 have S38: "w ∈ {v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⟷ 
	 w ∈ ℝ ∧ (\<cn>w) ∈ A" by auto (*rule MMI_elrab*)
       from S35 S38 have S39: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 w ∈ {v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⟶ 
	 (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_syl5ib)
       from S39 have S40: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
	 (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
	 w ∈ {v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⟶ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_com23)
     } then have S40: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶  (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
	 (∀ w. w ∈ {v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A } ⟶ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x))" by simp
     from S40 have S41: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       (∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> (\<cn>x))" by auto (*rule MMI_r19_21adv*)
     have S42: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ (\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
     from S41 S42 have S43: "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       (\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> (\<cn>x))" by (rule MMI_jctild)
     have S44: "z = (\<cn>x) ⟶ 
       w \<lsq> z ⟷ w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)" by (rule MMI_breq2)
     from S44 have S45: "z = (\<cn>x) ⟶ 
       (∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z) ⟷ 
       (∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> (\<cn>x))" by auto (*rule MMI_ralbidv*)
     from S45 have S46: "(\<cn>x) ∈ ℝ ∧ (∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> (\<cn>x)) ⟶ 
       ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z)" by auto (*rule MMI_rcla4ev*)
     from S43 S46 have "x ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
       (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z)" by (rule MMI_syl6)
   } then have S47: "∀ x. x ∈ ℝ ⟶ (∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
       ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z)"
     by simp
   from S47 have S48: "( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z)" by (rule MMI_r19_23aiv)
   from S48 have S49: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     ( ∃z∈ℝ. ∀w∈{v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A }. w \<lsq> z)" by (rule MMI_3ad2ant3)
   from S4 S26 S49 have S50: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_sylanc)
   have S51: "Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>) ∈ ℝ ⟶ 
     (\<cn>Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>)) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_renegclt)
   from S50 S51 have S52: "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     (\<cn>Sup({v ∈ ℝ. (\<cn>v) ∈ A },ℝ,\<cltrrset>)) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_syl)
   from S1 S52 show "A ⊆ℝ ∧ ¬(A = 0) ∧ ( ∃x∈ℝ. ∀y∈A. x \<lsq> y) ⟶ 
     Sup(A,ℝ,converse(\<cltrrset>)) ∈ ℝ" by (rule MMI_eqeltrd)
 qed
end
